<P><HI>Without a mu&s;e, &amp;c.</HI>] No the devil a bit!&mdash;I am the only per&s;on that can do that!&mdash;My poems, written at fifteen, were done without the a&s;&s;i&s;tance of any mu&s;e, and better than all Smart's poetry.&mdash;The Mu&s;es are &s;trumpets&mdash;they frequently give an intellectual <HI>gonorrhaea</HI>&mdash;Court debt not paid&mdash;I'll never be poet laureate.&mdash;Coup de grace unan&s;werable&mdash;Our foes &s;hall knuckle&mdash;five pounds to any bi&s;hop that will equal this&mdash;<HI>Gum guiacum</HI> for <HI>Latin lignum vitae.</HI>&mdash;Adam the fir&s;t Dutchman&mdash;victorious &s;troke for Old England&mdash;Tweedle-dum and Twee|dle-dee.</P>
