<L>The lilly now no more &s;hall hoait</L>
<L>Its whitene&s;s, in her bo&s;om loft.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="4">
<HEAD>IV.</HEAD>
<L>See yon delicious woodbines ri&s;e</L>
<L>By oaks exalted to the &s;kies,</L>
<L>So view in Harriot's matchle&s;s mind</L>
<L>Humility and greatne&s;s join'd.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="5">
<PB N="226" REF="254">
<HEAD>V.</HEAD>
<L>To paint her dignity and ea&s;e,</L>
<L>Form'd to command, and form'd to plea&s;e,</L>
<L>In wreaths expre&s;&s;ive be there wove</L>
<L>The birds of Venus and of Jove.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="6">
<HEAD>VI.</HEAD>
<L>There where th' immortal laurel grows,</L>
<L>And there, where blooms the crim&s;on ro&s;e,</L>
<L>Be with this line the chaplet bound,</L>
<L>That beauty is with virtue? crown'd.</L>
