<DIV1>
<HEAD>ODE to the EARL of NORTHUMERLAND,
On his being app inted Lord lieutenanr of Ireland,
Pre&s;ented on the Birth-Day of Lord Warkrworth.</HEAD>
<LG>
<L>WHATE'ER di&s;tingu&s;ih'd patriots ri&s;e,</L>
<L>The times and manners to revi&s;e,</L>
<L>And drooping merit rai&s;e,</L>
<L>The long of triumpa &s;til par&s;ues</L>
<L>Their fcot&s;teps, and the moral ma&s;e</L>
<L>Dwells &s;weetly on their prai&s;e.</L>
<L>It is a ta&s;k of true delight,</L>
