<DIV1>
<HEAD>THE SWEETS OF EVENING.</HEAD>
<LG>
<L>THE &s;weets of evening charm the mind,</L>
<L>Sick of the &s;ultry day;</L>
<L>The bodv then no more confin'd,</L>
<L>But exerci&s;e with freedom join'd,</L>
<L>When Phabus &s;heathes his ray.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>While all-&s;erene the &s;ummer moon</L>
<L>Sends glances thro' the trees,</L>
<L>And Philomel begins ker tune,</L>
<L>A&s;teria too &s;hall help her &s;oon</L>
<L>With voice of &s;kilful ea&s;e.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>A no&s;egay, every thing that grows,</L>
