<DIV1>
<HEAD>On a Lady throwing &startq;Snow-Balls at her Lover.
From the Latin of Petronious A&s;canius&endq;</HEAD>
<L>WHEN, wanton fair, the &s;nowy orb you throw,</L>
<L>I feel a fire before unknown in &s;now.</L>
<L>E'en colde&s;t &s;now I find has pow'r to warm</L>
<L>My brea&s;t, when flung by <HI>Julia's</HI> lovely arm.</L>
<L>T' elude loves powerful arts I &s;trive in vain,</L>
<L>If ice and &s;now can latent fires-contain.</L>
<L>'The&s;e frolicks leave: the force of beauty prove,</L>
